    <div class="content-section">
        <section id="Shaniwar Wada" class="section">
            <h2>Shaniwar Wada</h2>
            <img src="shaniwar-wada.jpg" alt="Shaniwar Wada" class="section-image">
            <p>Shaniwar Wada, located in Pune, Maharashtra, is a historical fort that once served as the seat of the Peshwa rulers. Built by Peshwa Bajirao I in 1732, it stands as a prominent example of Maratha architecture. The Wada, meaning "a dwelling," was the heart of the Peshwa government and a symbol of Pune's rich cultural heritage. </p>
            <p></p>
        </section>

        <section id="Aga Khan Palace" class="section">
            <h2>Aga Khan Palace</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Aga Khan Palace" class="section-image">
            <p>The Aga Khan Palace in Pune is a historical landmark renowned for its architectural beauty and significance in India's freedom movement. It was built in 1892 by Sultan Muhammed Shah Aga Khan III as a charitable act to provide employment during a famine. The palace is also known as the site of Mahatma Gandhi's imprisonment during the Quit India Movement. </p>
            <p></p>
        </section>

        <section id="Sinhagad Fort" class="section">
            <h2>Sinhagad Fort</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Sinhagad Fort" class="section-image">
            <p>Sinhagad Fort, also known as the "Lion's Fort", is a historic hill fortress located southwest of Pune, Maharashtra, India. It's known for its strategic location, rich history, and architectural features. The fort played a significant role in various battles, most notably the Battle of Sinhagad in 1670. </p>
            <p></p>
        </section>

        <section id="Raja Dinkar Kelkar Museum" class="section">
            <h2>Raja Dinkar Kelkar Museum</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Raja Dinkar Kelkar Museum" class="section-image">
            <p>The Raja Dinkar Kelkar Museum in Pune houses a vast collection of Indian artifacts, showcasing a rich cultural heritage. It was established by Dr. Dinkar G. Kelkar to honor his son, Raja, and contains over 20,000 items, including sculptures, paintings, and handicrafts. The museum is known for its diverse collection, spanning various materials like stone, wood, metal, ivory, fabric, and clay, and includes musical instruments, Mastani Mahal, and weaponry. </p>
        </section>

        <section id="Pataleshwar Cave Temple" class="section">
            <h2>Pataleshwar Cave Temple</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Pataleshwar Cave Temple" class="section-image">
            <p>The Raja Dinkar Kelkar Museum in Pune houses a vast collection of Indian artifacts, showcasing the country's rich artistic heritage. Founded by Dr. Dinkar G. Kelkar, the museum contains over 20,000 objects, including sculptures, paintings, and handicrafts, reflecting Indian everyday life. It's known for its diverse collection, including musical instruments, Mastani Mahal, and a variety of everyday objects from different eras. </p>
            <p></p>
        </section>

        <section id="Shinde Chhatri" class="section">
            <h2></h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Shinde Chhatri" class="section-image">
            <p>Shinde Chhatri, located in Wanowrie, Pune, is a memorial dedicated to the 18th-century Maratha military leader Mahadji Shinde. It's a beautifully constructed complex featuring a temple, samadhi (tomb), and a memorial structure. The site is known for its intricate carvings, paintings, and a blend of Anglo-Rajasthani architectural styles. </p>
            <p></p>
        </section>

        <section id="Tulshibaug & Market" class="section">
            <h2>Tulshibaug & Market</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Tulshibaug & Market" class="section-image">
            <p>Tulshibaug, also known as Tulsi Baug, is a bustling traditional market in Pune, famous for its wide variety of goods and budget-friendly shopping. Located near Laxmi Road, it stretches from Vishrambaug Wada to Shanipar and beyond. The market is known for its narrow lanes filled with shops selling everything from kitchenware and clothing to cosmetics and accessories. </p>
            <p></p>
        </section>

        <section id="Saras Baug" class="section">
            <h2>Saras Baug</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Saras Baug" class="section-image">
            <p>Saras Baug is a prominent landmark and park in Pune, India, known for its beautiful gardens, temple, and historical significance. It was originally a lake that dried up and was transformed into a 25-acre park. The park is home to the famous Saras Baug Ganpati temple, dedicated to Lord Ganesha. </p>
        </section>

        <section id="Parvati Hill" class="section">
            <h2>Parvati Hill</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Parvati Hill" class="section-image">
            <p>Parvati Hill is a prominent hillock and temple complex in Pune, Maharashtra, known for its historical and religious significance, as well as its panoramic city views. The hill is topped by the Parvati Temple, dedicated to Goddess Parvati and God Shiva, and also houses other temples dedicated to various deities. It's a popular spot for religious visits, trekking, and enjoying the scenery. </p>
            <p></p>
        </section>

        <section id="Koregaon Park & Osho Ashram" class="section">
            <h2>Koregaon Park & Osho Ashram</h2>
            <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Koregaon Park & Osho Ashram" class="section-image">
            <p>Koregaon Park in Pune is home to the Osho International Meditation Resort, a renowned spiritual center. The resort offers various meditation techniques, classes, and activities, attracting visitors worldwide. Non-members can purchase a one-day pass to experience the facilities. Osho Teerth Park, a free public park, is also located in Koregaon Park and is known for its serene environment and nature trails. </p>
            <p></p>
        </section>
